I don’t mean this video to be political in any way even though I know small minds will make it so… I heard this speech a few week before the project and it resonated with me. Resonated deeply. I always have been an outsider, been misunderstood, hated, laughed at…
I actually never climbed before. Castleton Tower was my very first climb, ever. What went into making it happen is way beyond what I want to share right now. May be later. But it took all of me, not just physically. I believe being authentic requires a certain level of mystery so I’ll keep the most heartfelt things to myself. I want to thank everyone who made this happen - you are true champions. I will never forget what you did for me and wherever I am in life I will remember you and always will be by your side whenever you need me. It was also an honor to wave The YO Ranch Flag - the most beautiful place I ever seen in Texas with so much heritage, culture and Texas Rangers’ tradition - the very heart of America I love. 
I’m doing what matters to me and that’s all that matters. Thank you All Thank You America. #freedom

It’s 1 am here, one of those nights when i just want to stay awake… I been thinking for sometime about what I want to share with you aside from the fact that disappointment has filled many gaps in friendships I used to cherish. 
For the past 9 years or so I shared my life on social media unconditionally, for many reasons. 
I developed an addiction - To posting, consuming, comparing … Oh no this is not one of those post blaming social media or someone else it’s myself I’m blaming. It’s always me not them. A few months before my life altering injury I felt an incredible urge to interrupt my use of this platform. I realized I was no longer SHARING MOMENTS - I was CREATING MOMENTS TO SHARE. Even though I tried to live trough them as much as I could I can’t deny the fact that the line between living and creating became incredibly thin. 
More than anything I want to own my soul. I’m an artist, - at least I dream to be one and remaining authentic, genuine - on and off this thing is vital to me.
 I appreciate everyone reaching out, I apologize for not opening your messages I am totally fine now. 
The solitude and silence is bringing me back to who I once was - present, aware, wholesome. I will never come back here again for no other reason but to share my creative endeavors without seeking any validation from people who really don’t give a damn - besides the moment they feel entertained by what they are swiping through. Through out this short time  I also realized that my privacy is my biggest privilege - we so desperately giving it away for the false sense of importance and validation … so no more senseless sharing where I’m at or who I’m with or what I’m eating. I enjoy not having my phone or feeling the urge to check it. Oh I missed this feeling! 
I am not looking to be any sort of character for any gain. I am unapologetically me now and forever. 
Happy Holidays.
